verses.text_plain: This then was the lot of the tribe of the children of Judah by their families; even to the border of Edom the wilderness of Zin southward was the uttermost part of the south coast.
verses.verse_html: 1This then was the lot of the tribe of the children of Judah by their families; even to the border of Edom the wilderness of Zin southward was the uttermost part of the south coast.

verses.text_plain: And their south border was from the shore of the salt sea, from the bay that looketh southward:
verses.verse_html:
2And their south border was from the shore of the salt sea, from the bay that looketh southward: ▼
▼ bay: Heb. tongue

verses.text_plain: And it went out to the south side to Maaleh–acrabbim, and passed along to Zin, and ascended up on the south side unto Kadesh–barnea, and passed along to Hezron, and went up to Adar, and fetched a compass to Karkaa:
verses.verse_html:
3And it went out to the south side to Maaleh–acrabbim, and passed along to Zin, and ascended up on the south side unto Kadesh–barnea, and passed along to Hezron, and went up to Adar, and fetched a compass to Karkaa: ▼
▼ Maaleh–acrabbim: or, the going up to Acrabbim

footnotes.body_text: ▼ Maaleh–acrabbim: or, the going up to Acrabbim
footnotes.body_html: ▼ Maaleh–acrabbim: or, the going up to Acrabbim

verses.text_plain: From thence it passed toward Azmon, and went out unto the river of Egypt; and the goings out of that coast were at the sea: this shall be your south coast.
verses.verse_html: 4From thence it passed toward Azmon, and went out unto the river of Egypt; and the goings out of that coast were at the sea: this shall be your south coast.

verses.text_plain: And the east border was the salt sea, even unto the end of Jordan. And their border in the north quarter was from the bay of the sea at the uttermost part of Jordan:
verses.verse_html: 5And the east border was the salt sea, even unto the end of Jordan. And their border in the north quarter was from the bay of the sea at the uttermost part of Jordan:

verses.text_plain: And the border went up to Beth–hogla, and passed along by the north of Beth–arabah; and the border went up to the stone of Bohan the son of Reuben:
verses.verse_html: 6And the border went up to Beth–hogla, and passed along by the north of Beth–arabah; and the border went up to the stone of Bohan the son of Reuben:

verses.text_plain: And the border went up toward Debir from the valley of Achor, and so northward, looking toward Gilgal, that is before the going up to Adummim, which is on the south side of the river: and the border passed toward the waters of En–shemesh, and the goings out thereof were at En–rogel:
verses.verse_html: 7And the border went up toward Debir from the valley of Achor, and so northward, looking toward Gilgal, that is before the going up to Adummim, which is on the south side of the river: and the border passed toward the waters of En–shemesh, and the goings out thereof were at En–rogel:

verses.text_plain: And the border went up by the valley of the son of Hinnom unto the south side of the Jebusite; the same is Jerusalem: and the border went up to the top of the mountain that lieth before the valley of Hinnom westward, which is at the end of the valley of the giants northward:
verses.verse_html: 8And the border went up by the valley of the son of Hinnom unto the south side of the Jebusite; the same is Jerusalem: and the border went up to the top of the mountain that lieth before the valley of Hinnom westward, which is at the end of the valley of the giants northward:

verses.text_plain: And the border was drawn from the top of the hill unto the fountain of the water of Nephtoah, and went out to the cities of mount Ephron; and the border was drawn to Baalah, which is Kirjath–jearim:
verses.verse_html: 9And the border was drawn from the top of the hill unto the fountain of the water of Nephtoah, and went out to the cities of mount Ephron; and the border was drawn to Baalah, which is Kirjath–jearim:

verses.text_plain: And the border compassed from Baalah westward unto mount Seir, and passed along unto the side of mount Jearim, which is Chesalon, on the north side, and went down to Beth–shemesh, and passed on to Timnah:
verses.verse_html: 10And the border compassed from Baalah westward unto mount Seir, and passed along unto the side of mount Jearim, which is Chesalon, on the north side, and went down to Beth–shemesh, and passed on to Timnah:

verses.text_plain: And the border went out unto the side of Ekron northward: and the border was drawn to Shicron, and passed along to mount Baalah, and went out unto Jabneel; and the goings out of the border were at the sea.
verses.verse_html: 11And the border went out unto the side of Ekron northward: and the border was drawn to Shicron, and passed along to mount Baalah, and went out unto Jabneel; and the goings out of the border were at the sea.

verses.text_plain: And the west border was to the great sea, and the coast thereof. This is the coast of the children of Judah round about according to their families.
verses.verse_html: 12And the west border was to the great sea, and the coast thereof. This is the coast of the children of Judah round about according to their families.

verses.text_plain: And unto Caleb the son of Jephunneh he gave a part among the children of Judah, according to the commandment of the Lord to Joshua, even the city of Arba the father of Anak, which city is Hebron.
verses.verse_html:
13And unto Caleb the son of Jephunneh he gave a part among the children of Judah, according to the commandment of the Lord to Joshua, even the city of Arba the father of Anak, which city is Hebron. ▼
▼ the city…: or, Kirjath–arba

footnotes.body_html: ▼ the city…: or, Kirjath–arba

verses.text_plain: And Caleb drove thence the three sons of Anak, Sheshai, and Ahiman, and Talmai, the children of Anak.
verses.verse_html: 14And Caleb drove thence the three sons of Anak, Sheshai, and Ahiman, and Talmai, the children of Anak.

verses.text_plain: And he went up thence to the inhabitants of Debir: and the name of Debir before was Kirjath–sepher.
verses.verse_html: 15And he went up thence to the inhabitants of Debir: and the name of Debir before was Kirjath–sepher.

verses.text_plain: And Caleb said, He that smiteth Kirjath–sepher, and taketh it, to him will I give Achsah my daughter to wife.
verses.verse_html: 16And Caleb said, He that smiteth Kirjath–sepher, and taketh it, to him will I give Achsah my daughter to wife.

tokens.text: it, to him will I give

verses.text_plain: And Othniel the son of Kenaz, the brother of Caleb, took it: and he gave him Achsah his daughter to wife.
verses.verse_html: 17And Othniel the son of Kenaz, the brother of Caleb, took it: and he gave him Achsah his daughter to wife.

verses.text_plain: And it came to pass, as she came unto him, that she moved him to ask of her father a field: and she lighted off her ass; and Caleb said unto her, What wouldest thou?
verses.verse_html: 18And it came to pass, as she came unto him, that she moved him to ask of her father a field: and she lighted off her ass; and Caleb said unto her, What wouldest thou?

tokens.text: And it came to pass, as she came

verses.text_plain: Who answered, Give me a blessing; for thou hast given me a south land; give me also springs of water. And he gave her the upper springs, and the nether springs.
verses.verse_html: 19Who answered, Give me a blessing; for thou hast given me a south land; give me also springs of water. And he gave her the upper springs, and the nether springs.

verses.text_plain: This is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Judah according to their families.
verses.verse_html: 20This is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Judah according to their families.

verses.text_plain: And the uttermost cities of the tribe of the children of Judah toward the coast of Edom southward were Kabzeel, and Eder, and Jagur,
verses.verse_html: 21And the uttermost cities of the tribe of the children of Judah toward the coast of Edom southward were Kabzeel, and Eder, and Jagur,

verses.text_plain: And Kinah, and Dimonah, and Adadah,
verses.verse_html: 22And Kinah, and Dimonah, and Adadah,

verses.text_plain: And Kedesh, and Hazor, and Ithnan,
verses.verse_html: 23And Kedesh, and Hazor, and Ithnan,

verses.text_plain: Ziph, and Telem, and Bealoth,
verses.verse_html: 24Ziph, and Telem, and Bealoth,

verses.text_plain: And Hazor, Hadattah, and Kerioth, and Hezron, which is Hazor,
verses.verse_html: 25And Hazor, Hadattah, and Kerioth, and Hezron, which is Hazor,

verses.text_plain: Amam, and Shema, and Moladah,
verses.verse_html: 26Amam, and Shema, and Moladah,

verses.text_plain: And Hazar–gaddah, and Heshmon, and Beth–palet,
verses.verse_html: 27And Hazar–gaddah, and Heshmon, and Beth–palet,

verses.text_plain: And Hazar–shual, and Beer–sheba, and Bizjothjah,
verses.verse_html: 28And Hazar–shual, and Beer–sheba, and Bizjothjah,

verses.text_plain: Baalah, and Iim, and Azem,
verses.verse_html: 29Baalah, and Iim, and Azem,

verses.text_plain: And Eltolad, and Chesil, and Hormah,
verses.verse_html: 30And Eltolad, and Chesil, and Hormah,

verses.text_plain: And Ziklag, and Madmannah, and Sansannah,
verses.verse_html: 31And Ziklag, and Madmannah, and Sansannah,

verses.text_plain: And Lebaoth, and Shilhim, and Ain, and Rimmon: all the cities are twenty and nine, with their villages:
verses.verse_html: 32And Lebaoth, and Shilhim, and Ain, and Rimmon: all the cities are twenty and nine, with their villages:

verses.text_plain: And in the valley, Eshtaol, and Zoreah, and Ashnah,
verses.verse_html: 33And in the valley, Eshtaol, and Zoreah, and Ashnah,

verses.text_plain: And Zanoah, and En–gannim, Tappuah, and Enam,
verses.verse_html: 34And Zanoah, and En–gannim, Tappuah, and Enam,

verses.text_plain: Jarmuth, and Adullam, Socoh, and Azekah,
verses.verse_html: 35Jarmuth, and Adullam, Socoh, and Azekah,

verses.text_plain: And Sharaim, and Adithaim, and Gederah, and Gederothaim; fourteen cities with their villages:
verses.verse_html:
36And Sharaim, and Adithaim, and Gederah, and Gederothaim; fourteen cities with their villages: ▼
▼ and Gederothaim: or, or Gederothaim

footnotes.body_html: ▼ and Gederothaim: or, or Gederothaim

verses.text_plain: Zenan, and Hadashah, and Migdal–gad,
verses.verse_html: 37Zenan, and Hadashah, and Migdal–gad,

verses.text_plain: And Dilean, and Mizpeh, and Joktheel,
verses.verse_html: 38And Dilean, and Mizpeh, and Joktheel,

verses.text_plain: Lachish, and Bozkath, and Eglon,
verses.verse_html: 39Lachish, and Bozkath, and Eglon,

verses.text_plain: And Cabbon, and Lahmam, and Kithlish,
verses.verse_html: 40And Cabbon, and Lahmam, and Kithlish,

verses.text_plain: And Gederoth, Beth–dagon, and Naamah, and Makkedah; sixteen cities with their villages:
verses.verse_html: 41And Gederoth, Beth–dagon, and Naamah, and Makkedah; sixteen cities with their villages:

verses.text_plain: Libnah, and Ether, and Ashan,
verses.verse_html: 42Libnah, and Ether, and Ashan,

verses.text_plain: And Jiphtah, and Ashnah, and Nezib,
verses.verse_html: 43And Jiphtah, and Ashnah, and Nezib,

verses.text_plain: And Keilah, and Achzib, and Mareshah; nine cities with their villages:
verses.verse_html: 44And Keilah, and Achzib, and Mareshah; nine cities with their villages:

verses.text_plain: Ekron, with her towns and her villages:
verses.verse_html: 45Ekron, with her towns and her villages:

verses.text_plain: From Ekron even unto the sea, all that lay near Ashdod, with their villages:
verses.verse_html:
46From Ekron even unto the sea, all that lay near Ashdod, with their villages: ▼
▼ near: Heb. by the place of

footnotes.body_text: ▼ near: Heb. by the place of
footnotes.body_html: ▼ near: Heb. by the place of

verses.text_plain: Ashdod with her towns and her villages, Gaza with her towns and her villages, unto the river of Egypt, and the great sea, and the border thereof:
verses.verse_html: 47Ashdod with her towns and her villages, Gaza with her towns and her villages, unto the river of Egypt, and the great sea, and the border thereof:

verses.text_plain: And in the mountains, Shamir, and Jattir, and Socoh,
verses.verse_html: 48And in the mountains, Shamir, and Jattir, and Socoh,

verses.text_plain: And Dannah, and Kirjath–sannah, which is Debir,
verses.verse_html: 49And Dannah, and Kirjath–sannah, which is Debir,

verses.text_plain: And Anab, and Eshtemoh, and Anim,
verses.verse_html: 50And Anab, and Eshtemoh, and Anim,

verses.text_plain: And Goshen, and Holon, and Giloh; eleven cities with their villages:
verses.verse_html: 51And Goshen, and Holon, and Giloh; eleven cities with their villages:

verses.text_plain: Arab, and Dumah, and Eshean,
verses.verse_html: 52Arab, and Dumah, and Eshean,

verses.text_plain: And Janum, and Beth–tappuah, and Aphekah,
verses.verse_html:
53And Janum, and Beth–tappuah, and Aphekah, ▼
▼ Janum: or, Janus

verses.text_plain: And Humtah, and Kirjath–arba, which is Hebron, and Zior; nine cities with their villages:
verses.verse_html: 54And Humtah, and Kirjath–arba, which is Hebron, and Zior; nine cities with their villages:

verses.text_plain: Maon, Carmel, and Ziph, and Juttah,
verses.verse_html: 55Maon, Carmel, and Ziph, and Juttah,

verses.text_plain: And Jezreel, and Jokdeam, and Zanoah,
verses.verse_html: 56And Jezreel, and Jokdeam, and Zanoah,

verses.text_plain: Cain, Gibeah, and Timnah; ten cities with their villages:
verses.verse_html: 57Cain, Gibeah, and Timnah; ten cities with their villages:

verses.text_plain: Halhul, Beth–zur, and Gedor,
verses.verse_html: 58Halhul, Beth–zur, and Gedor,

verses.text_plain: And Maarath, and Beth–anoth, and Eltekon; six cities with their villages:
verses.verse_html: 59And Maarath, and Beth–anoth, and Eltekon; six cities with their villages:

verses.text_plain: Kirjath–baal, which is Kirjath–jearim, and Rabbah; two cities with their villages:
verses.verse_html: 60Kirjath–baal, which is Kirjath–jearim, and Rabbah; two cities with their villages:

verses.text_plain: In the wilderness, Beth–arabah, Middin, and Secacah,
verses.verse_html: 61In the wilderness, Beth–arabah, Middin, and Secacah,

verses.text_plain: And Nibshan, and the city of Salt, and En–gedi; six cities with their villages.
verses.verse_html: 62And Nibshan, and the city of Salt, and En–gedi; six cities with their villages.

verses.text_plain: As for the Jebusites the inhabitants of Jerusalem, the children of Judah could not drive them out: but the Jebusites dwell with the children of Judah at Jerusalem unto this day.
verses.verse_html: 63As for the Jebusites the inhabitants of Jerusalem, the children of Judah could not drive them out: but the Jebusites dwell with the children of Judah at Jerusalem unto this day.
